OL,3,CConsumers set to get compensation for
OL,4,Cfaulty smart meters and install delays
OL,6,FIt comes as part of a crackdown on
OL,7,Fbroken smart meters, which has seen
OL,8,Fthe regulator help enforce the repair
OL,9,For replacement of more than 600,000
OL,10,Ffaulty meters since July last year.
OL,12,FMartin Lewis, MoneySavingExpert.com
OL,13,Ffounder, welcomed the proposals as he
OL,14,Fsaid "likely one in five" smart meters
OL,15,Fare faulty.
OL,17,FIt is thought that millions of smart
OL,18,Fmeters have been left in so-called
OL,19,Fdumb mode, where they have poor
OL,20,Fconnectivity or stop automatically
OL,21,Ftransmitting readings.
